          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL4JCDQIbRhj0M02GRcfIU36AKAaUtekpPYKloxBHuI7jKemQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100",
          "description": "1 STAR \u2014 THE MOST UNPROFESSIONAL CLINIC I\u2019VE EVER DEALT WITH\n\nI called MedRite specifically to ask if they do pre-op evaluations and provide surgery clearance letters. I was told YES. I came in, did all the tests, paid $300 upfront, and was assured by the front desk, MA, and PA that once my bloodwork was ready, they would send me my clearance letter immediately.\n\nIt\u2019s been over a week, and I still have NOTHING.\n\nI called to follow up and was told they would \u201csend the bloodwork\u201d but can\u2019t give me the clearance letter because the provider isn\u2019t in. Called again 3 days later \u2014 same excuse. Then I was told the other provider refuses to write the note. And finally, I was informed that they don\u2019t do clearance letters at all, even though ALL THREE staff members promised me they do.\n\nTo make it worse:\nThe $300 I paid does NOT even include the lab fees. The lab is now sending me another bill for the bloodwork. So I basically paid MedRite just to get my blood drawn, and in the end, received absolutely nothing I needed.\n\nThis place is misleading, unprofessional, and completely disorganized. They will say anything to take your money and then not deliver what they promise.\n\nSave your time and your money \u2014 go anywhere else.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT25kUWQzUlZVMUJVU2paNVJHeHplazVEWmxaQlVrRRAB!2m1!1s0x0:0x7e4be0884c9de85b!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOndQd3RVU1BUSjZ5RGxzek5DZlZBUkE%7C%7C?hl=en",
          "date": "6 months ago",
